.TH "t4vf_set_rxmode" 9 "t4vf_set_rxmode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
t4vf_set_rxmode \- set Rx properties of a virtual interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" t4vf_set_rxmode
.BI "(struct adapter *adapter "  ","
.BI "unsigned int viid "  ","
.BI "int mtu "  ","
.BI "int promisc "  ","
.BI "int all_multi "  ","
.BI "int bcast "  ","
.BI "int vlanex "  ","
.BI "bool sleep_ok "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adapter" 12
the adapter
.IP "viid" 12
the VI id
.IP "mtu" 12
the new MTU or -1 for no change
.IP "promisc" 12
1 to enable promiscuous mode, 0 to disable it, -1 no change
.IP "all_multi" 12
1 to enable all-multi mode, 0 to disable it, -1 no change
.IP "bcast" 12
1 to enable broadcast Rx, 0 to disable it, -1 no change
.IP "vlanex" 12
1 to enable hardware VLAN Tag extraction, 0 to disable it,
-1 no change
.IP "sleep_ok" 12
call is allowed to sleep

Sets Rx properties of a virtual interface.
